scala offers both MUTABLE and IMMUTABLE collections

*mutable collections can never be updated in place
*immutable collections never change

package object scala {
    type List[+A] = immutable.List[A]
    type Set[A] = immutable.Set[A]
}

* We use IMMUTABLE collections by default

IMMUTABLE COLLECTIONS: scala.collections.immutable

Traversable
    -Iterable
        -Seq
            -IndexedSeq
                *Vector
                *String
                *Range
            -LinearSeq
                *List
                *Stream
                *Stack
                *Queue
        -Set
            *HashSet
            *SortedSet
        -Map
            *HashMap
            *SortedMap


MUTABLE COLLECTIONS: scala.collections.mutable

Traversable
    -Iterable
        -Seq
            -IndexedSeq
                *StringBuilder
                *ArrayBuffer
            -Buffer
                *ArrayBuffer
                *ListBuffer
            -LinearSeq
                *LinkedList
                *MutableList
        -Set
            *HashSet
            *LinkedHashSet
        -Map
            *HashMap
            *MultiMap

Traversable
Base traits for all collections. Offers a great variety of methods

maps: map, flatMap, collect
conversions: toArray, toList, toSeq
size info: isEmpty, size, nonEmpty
tests : exists, forall
folds : foldLeft, foldRight, reduceLeft, reduceRight
retrieval : head, find, tail
string ops : mkString